                           <item xml:id="a2">
                              <locus target="#67ra"/>
                              <desc type="DonationNote">Donation note.</desc>
                              <q xml:lang="gez">
                                 <locus target="#67ra">67ra</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘመድኃኒ፡ ዓለም፡ አዲግራት፡ ዘወሀቦ፡
                              ዳግማዊ፡ ዘመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወምስለ፡ ብእሲቱ፡ ዓመተ፡ ድንግል፡ ከመ፡ ይኵኖሙ፡ መርሃ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡
                              ኦአንትሙ፡ ካህናት፡ ወዲያቆናት፡ ኢትርስዑነ፡ በጽሎትክሙ፡ ወበስዕለትክሙ፡ ተማኅፀነ፡ ንሕነ፡ ዘመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡
                              ዓመተ፡ ድንግል፡</q>
                           
                              <note> The note states that the Ms. was donated by Dāgǝmāwi Za-Manfas
                              Qǝddus and his wife ʾAmata Dǝngǝl. The note is written in the same
                              hand as the donation note in <ref type="mss" corresp="ESamm004">Ms. AMM-004 (s. Additio 3)</ref> and has a
                              similar content. Also, the same hand has added the names of the donors
                              into the supplication formulas in the headings of Texts I-2 to I-5
                              and, most probably, into the donation note in <ref type="mss" corresp="ESamm005">Ms. AMM-005</ref>. </note>
                           </item>
                           <item xml:id="a3">
                              <locus target="#102rb"/>
